<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-04-09T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-04-09T11:00:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.50 Recovery/4–948: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-04-09T11:00:00-05:00">April 9, 1948—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received—12:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Martel</hi> 36. I assume passage of ERP<note n="89" xml:id="d52fn89">European Recovery Program.</note> with China
                            assistance is the event which overtook the NSC paper. This should not
                            preclude consideration by defense establishment of views contained in my
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Martel</hi> 28.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>